g balance sheet investmentgrade credit ratings longterm contracts and a balanced approach to capital allocation diverse fuel sources and an everexpanding renewable energy portfolio our dedicated and experienced employees and management team we’re excited for the future and we’re ready to power many generations to come related documents transalta quickfacts brochure transalta australia quickfacts brochure transalta us quickfacts brochure aboriginal relations brochure related pages a message to our customers from dawn farrell sept  subscribe to our newsletterjoin our mailing list to receive the latest news and updates from our team subscribe you have successfully subscribed leadership  transalta select page leadership homeabout usleadership facilities news releases countries where we operate careers site map glossary accessibility ethics helpline terms and conditions of use customer solutions  everything energy for your business statement following government of alberta announcement contact form request a quote feedback talking about the future with albertans our people our values new richmond saintalphonse and caplan wholesale energy solutions facilitiesfeed about us clean power future coal to gas clean power transition governance leadership ceo message corporate officers board of directors values our history corporate structure innovation awards  achievements investors australia our business renewable energy sustainability leading us into the future   our team of corporate officers and senior managers have diverse industry experience in both regulated and deregulated markets team members understand the advantage of generating electricity from a variety of fuel sources and they know how to develop new projects integrate acquisitions operate in extreme and varied conditions improve efficiencies and to make the most of the power we create shareholders are represented by a board of directors that has a comprehensive understanding of the electricity resource finance and 