me with electrical lamps because of calgary power calgary powers cheap power is credited with canadian pacific railways decision to locate its regional engine repair shop in ogden calgary spurring calgarys economic development notable leaders from the company’s early years included w max aitken eventually lord beaverbrook and rb bennett who went on to become canada’s prime minister from  to  its monopoly position and behavior made its status as a private corporation unpopular among rural customers and some calgary residents and a move to nationalize it was converted to a provincewide referendum in  which came down very narrowly on the side of maintaining its private ownership in  the company changed its name to its current name of transalta corporation generation summary  megawatts mw of net capacity in operation  gigawatt hours gwh were produced at an average plant availability of  per cent for the year ended december   over  facilities in three geographies canada us australia one surface coal mine in operation highvale in alberta canada net capacity owned by fuel type in operation and in development type net capacity coal  gas  wind  hydro  geothermal  net capacity owned by geography in operation and development geography net capacity canada  united states  australia  at the end of  transalta became the first company to own and operate more than  mw of installed wind capacity in canada  almost  per cent of the countrys total ghost river reservoiredit after the  alberta floods as a temporary partial solution to mitigate flood damage during those months when there is a greater risk of rising water that might cause flooding the government pays transalta corporation  million to lower the level of water on its ghost reservoir a temporary deal between the government and transalta corp that pays the utility m to lower water levels on its ghost reservoir for two months this year when the risk of rising water looms largest offers a partial solution controversiesedit in  and  transalta timed their power outages so as to drive up prices of electricity and increase their revenues the alberta utilities commission declared these acts illegal in their review concluded on july   the commission has yet to determine penalties for this manipulation of the energy markets hydro facilities in british columbiaedit upper mamquam built by canadian hydro developers and operational in  it is a runoftheriver hydroelectric plant km northeast of squamish bc the penstock is  km long dropping  meters to the powerhouse containing two  mw pelton wheel generators bone creek flows into the north thompson river the hydroelectric plant constructed in  has a km penstock dropping  meters to a powerhouse with two gw francis turbines it is located  km south of valemount bc operating as valisa energy inc approximately  gwh of power annually is sold to bc hydro akolkolex was built by canadian hydro developers and operational in  it uses two francis turbines in a  mw runofriver hydroelectric plant discharging into arrow lakes it is located  km se of revelstoke bc the plant produces approximately  gwh of electricity annually pingston creek has a  meter high sheetpile rock fill dam which diverts water to the western shore of arrow lakes it was built by canadian hydro developers and brascan power and began operation as pingston power inc in  a km tunnel achieves a huge drop of  meters to three  mw pelton wheels to generate about  gwh annually the project is km south of revelstoke bc °′″n °′″w﻿  ﻿°n °w﻿    referencesedit  jennings a owen  merchants and manufacturers record of calgary calgary jennings publishing company p    foran max  calgary canadas frontier metropolis  an illustrated history windsor publications p  isbn    mcclure matt  june  residents upset over lack of plan for flooding threat calgary herald calgary retrieved  june    transalta timed power outages to drive up prices alberta commission global news retrieved  july    httpwwwindustcardscomhydrocanadabchtm